@startuml Container Diagram
' Workflow test - updated
!define RECTANGLE class
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

title Employee Management System - Container Diagram

package "External Systems" #LightBlue {
  [GitHub] as GitHub
  [Docker Hub] as DockerHub
  [AWS Cloud] as AWS
}

actor "User" as User

package "Employee Management System" #LightYellow {
  [Angular Web Application] as Web
  [Nginx Gateway] as Gateway
  [Spring Boot API] as API
  database "PostgreSQL Database" as DB
  database "Redis" as Redis

  note right of Web
    **Technology:** Angular 19, TypeScript
    **Port:** 80
    **Purpose:** User interface
    **Features:**
    - Employee Management
    - Department Management
    - Dashboard
    - Project Management
  end note

  note right of Gateway
    **Technology:** Nginx
    **Purpose:** API Gateway, routing, security
    **Features:**
    - IP blocklist (return 444)
    - Rate limiting (auth: 10r/m, api: 20r/s)
    - Connection limiting (10 per IP)
    - Request routing & API proxying
    - Static file serving
    - TLS termination
  end note

  note right of API
    **Technology:** Java 17, Spring Boot 3.4
    **Port:** 8080
    **Purpose:** REST API
    **Features:**
    - Employee CRUD
    - Department CRUD
    - Dashboard metrics
    - Project/Task management
  end note

  note right of DB
    **Technology:** PostgreSQL 15
    **Port:** 5432
    **Purpose:** Data storage
    **Features:**
    - Employee data
    - Department data
    - Project/Task data
  end note

  note right of Redis
    **Technology:** Redis 7
    **Port:** 6379
    **Purpose:** Distributed rate limiting
    **Features:**
    - Token bucket per IP
    - Auth: 10 req/min
    - API: 100 req/min
    - 1hr TTL on auth keys
  end note
}

User --> Web : Uses
Web --> Gateway : Served by
Gateway --> API : Proxies API requests\n(after rate limit check)
API --> DB : Reads/Writes
Gateway --> Web : Serves static files
API --> Redis : Rate limit state

GitHub --> Web : CI/CD
GitHub --> API : CI/CD
API --> DockerHub : Pushes images
Web --> DockerHub : Pushes images
DockerHub --> AWS : Pulls for deployment

@enduml
